<title>UK: UK home buying costs to jump 20% in 1997 - TSB.</title>
<headline>UK home buying costs to jump 20% in 1997 - TSB.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-12-11</dateline>
<text>
<p>The cost of buying a home in Britain will rocket by 20 percent next year, the TSB Bank said on Wednesday.</p>
<p>As mortgage rates and house prices rise, typical buyers will be spending 30.70 stg of every 100 pounds of net income on a mortgage by the end of 1997, TSB, now part of LLoyds TSB Group, said.</p>
<p>That would be the highest level for nearly five years but well below the 71.30 peak seen in 1991, it said. This year, buyers spent an average 25.60 stg of every 100 pounds of income on mortgages.</p>
